The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to predict human decision-making behavior based on well-established behavioral theories. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on the application of these techniques to behavioral fields, which could place it in the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper's focus on predicting human decision-making behavior could also place it in the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
